  "description": "The load-bearing invariant: evidence never flips verifyRecord().valid. A correctly signed record is verified alongside failing OAuth authorization evidence (scope attenuation failure under caller-verified claims). The evidence block and its mapped envelope MUST carry valid: false while the record itself stays valid: true. A signed action is real even when its external evidence is missing, expired, over-scoped, or forged; consumers apply their own policy over tiers.",
